  "text": "The Envoy HTTP filter chain configuration propagation works as follows:\n\n## Protobuf Definitions (data-plane-api)\n\nThe primary configuration is defined in **envoyproxy/data-plane-api** at `envoy/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/v3/http_connection_manager.proto`:\n\n1. **HttpConnectionManager** (line 41+): The main message that configures HTTP connection handling. It contains a field `repeated HttpFilter http_filters = 5` (line 471 in data-plane-api version) which defines the filter chain - an ordered list of HTTP filters to process requests sequentially.\n\n2. **HttpFilter** (line 1339+): Individual filter configuration message containing:\n   - `string name` - The filter name to instantiate\n   - `oneof config_type` with `google.protobuf.Any typed_config` - Filter-specific configuration\n   - `bool disabled` - Whether filter is disabled by default\n   - `bool is_optional` - Whether filter is optional\n\n3. **UpgradeConfig** (line 316+): Contains upgrade-specific filter chains with `repeated HttpFilter filters = 2`\n\nA legacy v2 version exists at `envoy/config/filter/network/http_connection_manager/v2/http_connection_manager.proto`.\n\n## C++ Implementation (envoy)\n\nThe configuration consumption happens through these key components:\n\n### 1. Factory Entry Point\n**envoyproxy/envoy** `source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h`:\n- **HttpConnectionManagerFilterConfigFactory**: The network filter factory that creates HCM instances. It implements `createFilterFactoryFromProtoTyped()` taking the protobuf config as input.\n\n### 2. Configuration Parsing\n**source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h** and **config.cc**:\n- **HttpConnectionManagerConfig**: Maps the protobuf config to runtime config. The constructor (config.cc line ~500+) orchestrates the entire configuration parsing including filter chain initialization.\n- Includes the proto-generated header: `#include \"envoy/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/v3/http_connection_manager.pb.h\"`\n- Processes `config.http_filters()` through the FilterChainHelper at line 714 in config.cc\n\n### 3. Filter Chain Processing\n**source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h**:\n- **FilterChainHelper<FilterCtx, NeutralNamedHttpFilterFactory>**: Template class that processes the repeated HttpFilter field. Key methods:\n  - `processFilters()` (lines 87-102): Iterates through the HttpFilter list and processes each one\n  - `processFilter()` (lines 105-165): Processes individual filters, looking up factories, translating config, and creating filter factory callbacks\n  - `processDynamicFilterConfig()`: Handles dynamic filter configuration (ECDS)\n\n- **FilterChainUtility**: Contains utilities for creating filter chains, including:\n  - Type definition: `using FiltersList = Protobuf::RepeatedPtrField<envoy::extensions::filters::network::http_connection_manager::v3::HttpFilter>` (lines 52-53)\n  - `createFilterChainForFactories()`: Instantiates filters using the created factory callbacks\n\n## Configuration Flow\n\n1. Protobuf HttpConnectionManager message arrives at factory\n2. HttpConnectionManagerFilterConfigFactory creates HttpConnectionManagerConfig\n3. HttpConnectionManagerConfig constructor calls FilterChainHelper::processFilters() with `config.http_filters()`\n4. FilterChainHelper iterates through each HttpFilter message:\n   - Retrieves the filter factory by name\n   - Translates the typed_config to the factory's expected message type\n   - Calls factory->createFilterFactoryFromProto() to get a FilterFactoryCb\n   - Validates filter dependencies and terminal filter constraints\n5. FilterChainUtility uses collected FilterFactoryCbs to instantiate filters at request time\n6. HTTP requests then flow through the filter chain in the configured order\n\nThe same pattern applies to upgrade_configs, where filter chains can be configured per-upgrade type."
}

